\begin{abstract}
  We extend standard $\kdotp$ theory to take into account periodic
  perturbations which are rapidly oscillating with a wavelength of a few
  lattice constants. Our general formalism allows us to explicitly
  consider the Bragg reflections due to the perturbation-induced
  periodicity.  As an example we calculate the effective masses in the
  lowest two conduction bands of spontaneously ordered GaInP$_{2}$ as a
  function of the degree of ordering. Comparison of our results for the
  lowest conduction band to available experimental data and to first
  principle calculations shows good agreement.
\end{abstract}

